## Risk Management

- **Risk:** Data loss due to improper handling of the USB drive during the recovery process.
  - **Mitigation Strategy:** Use a disk image for all recovery attempts, leaving the original USB drive untouched.

---

## Retrospective

- **What Went Well:** Developed a thorough plan for attempting data recovery using advanced forensic techniques.
- **What Could Be Improved:** Time management could be better, as more time could have been dedicated to experimenting with the actual recovery tools.
- **Actionable Insights:** Prioritize creating disk images before attempting any forensic recovery to ensure the integrity of the original data.

